Lastly, it would be contrary to reason to suppose that the process of corruptionโwhether mechanical, arising from the development of a blunder, due originally to a slip of the pen, or semi-intelligent, owing to the addition of variants from other MSS. by the corrector-such as is revealed to us in the gradual formation of the inferior text, was not equally operative in the preceding silent centuries. The best MS. has its limitations, audit is well to recognise the insufficiency of our guides.
